WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:37.768 --> 00:40.061
I'm not someone
who will leave in three months,

00:40.062 --> 00:42.772
nor someone who might never come back.

00:42.773 --> 00:44.523
Ms. Song, I want to stay

00:44.524 --> 00:45.567
with you.

00:46.568 --> 00:48.945
No, Haran. So I'll tell you everything.

00:49.696 --> 00:53.199
But to tell you everything precisely,

00:53.200 --> 00:54.909
I need some time.

00:54.910 --> 00:55.952
It won't take long.

00:56.536 --> 00:59.247
I'll tell you everything honestly soon.

00:59.748 --> 01:01.708
So when I do,

01:02.459 --> 01:03.834
please listen to everything.

01:05.712 --> 01:07.296
What if you're not okay?

01:07.297 --> 01:08.923
What if something else happens?

01:08.924 --> 01:11.884
I've been okay, I'm okay now,
and I'll keep being okay.

01:11.885 --> 01:12.886
So…

01:14.471 --> 01:15.472
let's go see

01:18.392 --> 01:20.310
the cherry blossoms in spring.

01:21.186 --> 01:23.854
We'll have shaved ice in summer,

01:23.855 --> 01:26.024
see the autumn leaves in fall,

01:26.858 --> 01:28.068
and in winter…

01:29.903 --> 01:31.655
it would be fun to go snowboarding.

01:38.995 --> 01:40.871
EPISODE 10

01:45.585 --> 01:47.545
I think you dropped your bracelet.

01:48.630 --> 01:49.798
This is yours, right?

01:52.884 --> 01:55.595
Oh. Hey, crybaby Song Haran.

02:15.323 --> 02:17.868
- Let's go.
- Let me return her bracelet.

02:21.163 --> 02:24.124
Oh, no. I'm sorry. Oh…

02:25.375 --> 02:27.794
Get your stuff. I'll do this.

02:30.088 --> 02:31.505
I came to ask you for help.

02:31.506 --> 02:33.424
I really want to protect something,

02:33.425 --> 02:35.885
but to do that, I need my memories.

02:36.970 --> 02:39.054
It's okay. It breaks sometimes.

02:39.055 --> 02:41.516
I've been wearing it for a long time.

02:43.727 --> 02:44.811
I'm sorry.

02:46.188 --> 02:48.731
I'm sorry, I'll get it repaired for you.

02:48.732 --> 02:51.401
It's really fine, Haran.

02:53.904 --> 02:54.987
Excuse me?

02:54.988 --> 02:57.199
Ah. Your name was written on the pen.

02:58.325 --> 02:59.576
That's a pretty name.

03:01.119 --> 03:04.288
- Let's go.
- He seems to be in quite a hurry.

03:04.289 --> 03:05.665
You can go. It's fine.

03:07.667 --> 03:09.211
I'm really sorry…

03:11.087 --> 03:12.380
Why are you so on edge?

03:14.090 --> 03:17.843
No, wait. I'm sorry.
You should hurry home and get some rest.

03:17.844 --> 03:19.554
Did the doctor say you're okay?

03:20.222 --> 03:21.223
Yes, I'm fine.

03:21.723 --> 03:22.766
So let's go.

03:37.572 --> 03:40.659
If you feel dizzy or uncomfortable,
tell me straightaway.

03:48.667 --> 03:49.668
Sir.

03:50.168 --> 03:52.546
I'm sorry, but can you pull over nearby?

03:53.713 --> 03:55.382
Shouldn't you get some rest?

03:55.882 --> 03:56.967
I'm totally fine.

03:58.260 --> 04:01.263
Oh? There's a look of doubt on your face.

04:02.222 --> 04:05.474
Then I'll do 100 push-ups!

04:06.560 --> 04:08.519
All right, fine. I believe you.

04:08.520 --> 04:12.399
I feel like we'll just feel down
and regret it if we go home now.

04:12.899 --> 04:13.983
So…

04:15.777 --> 04:19.531
let's begin Seonu Chan's
birthday gift ceremony.

04:22.534 --> 04:24.244
That's my present, right?

04:25.120 --> 04:26.537
This…

04:26.538 --> 04:27.789
Oh… Let me guess.

04:28.373 --> 04:31.167
Mmm… It's clothes.

04:31.877 --> 04:35.297
A cardigan you designed yourself.

04:35.922 --> 04:37.673
How did you know?

04:37.674 --> 04:39.133
I prepared this in secret.

04:39.134 --> 04:41.010
It was obvious.

04:41.011 --> 04:42.137
It was?

04:43.263 --> 04:45.307
Oh. I see…

04:46.683 --> 04:49.436
Hang on. Just give me five minutes.

04:51.313 --> 04:57.651
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

04:57.652 --> 05:01.113
♪ Happy birthday, dear Seonu Chan ♪

05:01.114 --> 05:03.282
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

05:04.701 --> 05:06.160
Wait.

05:06.161 --> 05:08.078
You should still make a wish

05:08.079 --> 05:10.998
even if it's just a humble
convenience store cake.

05:10.999 --> 05:12.667
Then make a wish with me.

05:25.180 --> 05:27.181
Wow!

05:27.182 --> 05:28.433
What did you wish for?

05:29.017 --> 05:31.852
It's a secret.
If I share it, it won't come true.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.395
Right.

05:33.396 --> 05:35.272
Then…

05:35.273 --> 05:38.025
I'll give you your birthday present now.

05:38.026 --> 05:40.362
- Happy birthday.
- Oh. Can I open it right now?

05:48.286 --> 05:49.620
Huh?

05:49.621 --> 05:52.581
I didn't know about this.

05:52.582 --> 05:54.626
At least
I kept one thing a secret.

05:57.212 --> 05:58.463
I'm glad I was born.

06:00.215 --> 06:02.425
Song Haran wished me happy birthday.

06:04.135 --> 06:07.180
Everybody!
Song Haran wished me happy birthday!

06:08.098 --> 06:09.974
Are you crazy?

06:11.226 --> 06:15.020
I'll wear this every day,
in spring, summer, fall, and winter.

06:15.021 --> 06:17.106
I'll wear this to bed, too.

06:17.107 --> 06:20.819
Ah. And even when I'm showering.

06:21.695 --> 06:25.073
I wanted to do more for you
since it's our first birthday together.

06:28.451 --> 06:29.995
Since you seem upset,

06:30.704 --> 06:31.787
how about a date tomorrow?

06:31.788 --> 06:34.790
We can watch a movie,
have a nice meal, hold hands,

06:34.791 --> 06:37.126
and take a walk while we chat.

06:37.127 --> 06:38.795
We'll do what other couples do.

06:39.879 --> 06:42.465
You should just rest. I'm worried.

06:43.049 --> 06:46.677
You leave me
no choice, then. I should do push-ups…

06:46.678 --> 06:49.680
All right. Let's go on a date.

06:51.015 --> 06:55.770
But can you sing that part again?

06:56.646 --> 06:57.980
The…

06:57.981 --> 07:00.859
"dear Seonu Chan" part.

07:03.486 --> 07:06.113
I'll make your birthday
even more special next year.

07:06.114 --> 07:09.367
I'm going to use that trial
for the rest of my life.

07:14.539 --> 07:15.540
So…

07:17.041 --> 07:18.793
stay healthy, okay?

07:26.968 --> 07:28.428
I will.

07:29.554 --> 07:30.680
Besides,

07:31.264 --> 07:34.184
my mind's filled with you, Haran,

07:35.477 --> 07:38.146
so a tiny fragment in my brain…

07:39.063 --> 07:41.107
won't affect me.

07:56.039 --> 07:57.289
Sir?

07:57.290 --> 07:58.583
Just a moment.

08:12.597 --> 08:13.932
What?

08:14.641 --> 08:15.725
Why are we…

08:17.769 --> 08:19.938
We were in Chuncheon earlier…

08:24.651 --> 08:25.860
Manjae.

08:27.320 --> 08:29.697
We're here. Let's get off.

08:41.668 --> 08:42.919
How long has it been?

08:43.545 --> 08:44.796
Where were you planning

08:46.256 --> 08:47.924
to disappear off to alone?

08:48.842 --> 08:49.926
Manjae.

08:51.719 --> 08:52.804
What do I do?

08:55.014 --> 08:56.349
What do I do about the kids?

09:00.854 --> 09:01.855
I want

09:02.939 --> 09:05.233
to stay with them longer.

09:08.069 --> 09:10.864
I want to stay with you longer, too.

09:12.782 --> 09:14.659
But what if I forget everything?

09:16.870 --> 09:19.372
If I end up
forgetting you and the kids…

09:23.751 --> 09:26.045
and everything else…

09:29.340 --> 09:30.466
I'm scared.

09:31.259 --> 09:32.802
I'm terrified.

09:38.808 --> 09:39.809
It's all right.

09:40.435 --> 09:41.853
Everything will be okay.

09:42.979 --> 09:46.149
You can let it all out with me.

09:48.109 --> 09:49.110
Don't worry.

09:49.819 --> 09:50.945
I will never

09:51.821 --> 09:53.072
let you be alone.

09:54.908 --> 09:56.158
Never.

10:14.552 --> 10:17.096
There's one missing.

10:23.853 --> 10:24.937
Huh?

10:28.566 --> 10:31.361
I took one of her charms.

10:31.945 --> 10:33.321
How do I get this back to her?

10:37.659 --> 10:40.245
The shrapnel's still lodged deep
in the temporal bone.

10:53.007 --> 10:54.217
It's really fine,

10:54.801 --> 10:55.802
Haran.

11:05.645 --> 11:06.854
What did you wish for?

11:07.814 --> 11:10.275
I won't wish for anything else
for the rest of my life.

11:11.192 --> 11:13.485
Please just let me stay with this person

11:13.486 --> 11:15.988
who let me live again,

11:15.989 --> 11:19.450
through every tear and every smile.

11:19.993 --> 11:22.745
I'm going to use that trial
for the rest of my life.

11:23.288 --> 11:25.164
Just allow me this one thing.

11:26.082 --> 11:28.167
Let me keep staying by her side.

11:48.313 --> 11:53.776
My birthday, the day I decided
to explain everything,

11:54.527 --> 11:55.945
despite the gaps.

12:12.962 --> 12:14.881
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

12:18.843 --> 12:20.636
PETROUS PART OF THE TEMPORAL BONE

12:22.430 --> 12:25.016
Your sister's coming in.

12:26.517 --> 12:27.851
What?

12:27.852 --> 12:30.103
Are you applying for medical school, too?

12:30.104 --> 12:31.521
I was just looking up something.

12:31.522 --> 12:32.689
Is Grandma still sleeping?

12:32.690 --> 12:36.651
Yeah, it's the first time.
She never slept in, even on the weekends.

12:36.652 --> 12:39.405
Is she tired
after her trip to Chuncheon?

12:40.031 --> 12:41.448
But what are those books for?

12:41.449 --> 12:44.743
I just thought I'd work
to get my mind off things.

12:44.744 --> 12:48.372
Do you have the pigment book?
It wasn't in Grandma's study.

12:48.373 --> 12:51.125
It's probably in the attic. Hmm…

12:52.126 --> 12:53.961
Why are your eyes puffy? Did you cry?

12:54.837 --> 12:56.380
Huh?

12:56.381 --> 12:58.924
Of course not.
I just slept well.

12:58.925 --> 13:00.927
Just go and find that book for me.

13:03.179 --> 13:04.305
Thank you.

13:15.441 --> 13:17.068
You can overcome it.

13:18.152 --> 13:20.238
You'll be able to escape on your own.

13:21.030 --> 13:22.531
I wanted to show you, too.

13:31.582 --> 13:34.709
What are you doing?
Why did you pull up your sleeves?

13:34.710 --> 13:36.711
I want to clear out some stuff.

13:36.712 --> 13:38.088
Like a spring deep clean.

13:38.089 --> 13:41.592
Get your head together.
It's the middle of winter.

13:42.635 --> 13:45.471
No, it's spring.

13:51.310 --> 13:53.855
I don't think I'll wear this.

13:55.940 --> 13:57.150
And this…

14:09.370 --> 14:11.247
- I'm heading out.
- Wait.

14:11.831 --> 14:13.707
-  You've got mail.
- Oh?

14:13.708 --> 14:16.668
He must have sent a letter
since it's so hard to reach you.

14:16.669 --> 14:19.296
That poor Kang Hyeokchan.

14:19.297 --> 14:20.881
- See you later.
- Huh?

14:20.882 --> 14:22.967
You're right. Oh…

14:24.427 --> 14:25.428
Yes?

14:25.970 --> 14:27.638
I'll be there right away.

14:38.399 --> 14:41.443
Haran, you must still be busy.

14:41.444 --> 14:44.821
It's already been a month
since I came to Boston.

14:44.822 --> 14:47.073
Everything still feels unfamiliar to me.

14:47.074 --> 14:50.827
I miss you, but it's hard to hear
your voice because of the time difference.

14:50.828 --> 14:53.079
I've been thinking
about a way to communicate.

14:53.080 --> 14:54.998
Can you use a messenger at work?

14:54.999 --> 14:56.042
Tell me if you can.

14:56.709 --> 14:58.044
Ah. Let me tell you something cool.

14:58.628 --> 15:00.921
My dorm roommate is Korean,

15:00.922 --> 15:02.464
and his name's Chan, too.

15:02.465 --> 15:03.633
Isn't that funny?

15:04.300 --> 15:06.760
But I think it'll be hard
to get close to him.

15:06.761 --> 15:08.846
He seems a bit closed off.

15:09.430 --> 15:11.264
I miss you so much, Haran.

15:11.265 --> 15:13.433
I'll come see you during summer break.

15:13.434 --> 15:15.519
Take care. I love you.

15:20.900 --> 15:23.610
I booked the movie tickets.
I'll see you at 5:00 p.m.

15:23.611 --> 15:25.571
Oh. I should get ready.

15:39.752 --> 15:40.961
Mr. Park.

15:40.962 --> 15:43.881
I might come home pretty late tonight.

15:46.717 --> 15:48.593
All right.

15:48.594 --> 15:51.429
Talk it out with Haran.

15:51.430 --> 15:55.434
If you're sincere,
I'm sure she'll understand.

16:00.231 --> 16:02.275
- All right. I will.
- Okay.

16:15.121 --> 16:16.746
They must be in the corner.

16:16.747 --> 16:19.917
This is broken.
It won't charge.

16:27.800 --> 16:30.219
Do you have time
after the movie?

16:31.554 --> 16:33.472
There's something I have to tell you.

16:34.473 --> 16:37.727
I'll tell you everything honestly soon.

16:39.687 --> 16:40.896
All right.

16:42.648 --> 16:45.108
Oh? I forgot the other popcorn.

16:45.109 --> 16:46.818
I'll go get it.

16:46.819 --> 16:49.155
- Just wait here.
- I'll wait inside, then.

17:01.709 --> 17:03.711
-  Sorry about that.
- It's okay.

17:04.211 --> 17:05.212
Thank you.

17:09.175 --> 17:11.217
- Is it a false alarm?
- What do we do?

17:11.218 --> 17:13.804
Please follow the instructions
and evacuate immediately.

17:14.430 --> 17:15.513
Please don't push.

17:15.514 --> 17:16.557
Song Haran.

17:17.892 --> 17:19.018
Please go downstairs.

17:19.852 --> 17:21.436
Don't push!

17:26.067 --> 17:27.777
Evacuate immediately.

17:29.528 --> 17:31.237
You shouldn't go inside.

17:31.238 --> 17:32.322
Sorry!

17:32.323 --> 17:33.449
- Sir!
- Song Haran!

17:34.700 --> 17:35.992
Song Haran!

17:45.753 --> 17:47.213
Stop it!

17:59.892 --> 18:01.102
Seonu Chan!

18:03.646 --> 18:05.606
Seonu Chan!

18:06.107 --> 18:07.190
I'll tell you everything.

18:07.191 --> 18:10.443
I'll tell you about the scars on my body.

18:10.444 --> 18:12.655
I don't do well in noisy places.

18:14.323 --> 18:16.409
Seonu Chan! Where are you?

18:23.207 --> 18:25.458
Where were you?

18:25.459 --> 18:26.835
I couldn't see you outside,

18:26.836 --> 18:28.754
- so I thought you'd gone inside…
- I'm okay.

18:29.422 --> 18:32.174
I'm so relieved nothing happened.

18:36.721 --> 18:37.930
It's okay.

18:38.681 --> 18:40.348
Let's go to the hospital
and get you checked.

18:40.349 --> 18:42.435
I'll get a checkup soon.

18:42.935 --> 18:44.562
Don't worry.

18:45.771 --> 18:47.648
I'll be completely fine.

18:57.408 --> 18:59.409
MEDICAL CHECKUP

19:02.747 --> 19:04.080
Grandma.

19:04.081 --> 19:06.208
What is it, Haran? Is something wrong?

19:11.255 --> 19:12.380
What do I do, Grandma?

19:13.674 --> 19:15.801
He's not well.

19:17.011 --> 19:18.888
He keeps collapsing,

19:19.889 --> 19:21.974
and there's something lodged in his head.

19:22.767 --> 19:25.269
He says he's okay,
but he doesn't seem okay at all.

19:26.395 --> 19:29.023
What do I do
if something happens to him?

19:30.274 --> 19:32.233
I may not be

19:32.234 --> 19:35.988
as good for her as you believe.

19:42.912 --> 19:44.580
He's not keeping it from you.

19:45.289 --> 19:46.457
He probably can't

19:47.249 --> 19:48.250
because he's scared.

19:48.918 --> 19:51.504
He probably doesn't want
to burden you with his pain

19:52.171 --> 19:53.630
because it would hurt you.

19:53.631 --> 19:54.757
He cares more

19:55.591 --> 19:58.051
about protecting you than his own pain.

19:58.052 --> 20:00.095
But I want to protect him.

20:01.263 --> 20:03.432
I don't want him to go through it alone.

20:04.683 --> 20:07.143
But there's nothing I can do for him.

20:07.144 --> 20:08.854
Just stay by his side.

20:09.563 --> 20:13.484
People can stay strong
even with just one person by their side.

20:14.026 --> 20:15.069
Trust me, I know.

20:16.195 --> 20:18.863
So don't worry too much.

20:18.864 --> 20:21.742
I'm sure you'll find a way.

20:38.384 --> 20:39.385
Waste container…

20:40.010 --> 20:41.178
Kang Hyeokchan…

20:41.762 --> 20:42.805
Lab…

20:43.556 --> 20:44.806
Cha Sujin…

20:47.476 --> 20:48.602
Stop it!

20:49.270 --> 20:50.437
And me…

20:51.939 --> 20:53.691
Was that day…

20:57.862 --> 21:00.697
"Volatile reagent container fractured…"

21:00.698 --> 21:02.407
"Self-reactive event

21:02.408 --> 21:05.202
triggered by careless handling
of reagents."

21:05.703 --> 21:09.247
"The cause has not been
conclusively determined."

21:09.248 --> 21:10.331
No, there's nothing.

21:10.332 --> 21:11.958
I said I don't know!

21:13.752 --> 21:17.548
What is she trying to hide?

21:25.347 --> 21:27.265
Don't do anything tomorrow

21:27.266 --> 21:29.183
and get plenty of rest.

21:29.184 --> 21:30.978
I'll always be by your side.

21:38.777 --> 21:42.406
MY BIRTHDAY, THE DAY I DECIDED
TO EXPLAIN EVERYTHING, DESPITE THE GAPS

21:45.367 --> 21:47.912
KANG HYEOKCHAN
CHA SUJIN

21:59.840 --> 22:01.842
12-WEEK REHABILITATION PLAN

22:02.384 --> 22:04.595
Ah. It's tomorrow.

22:05.179 --> 22:09.474
But, Mr. Park, when should we tell
Hadam and her sisters?

22:09.475 --> 22:10.975
Yougyum!

22:10.976 --> 22:12.435
Hey, Dad!

22:12.436 --> 22:13.603
Really? Okay.

22:13.604 --> 22:15.146
Is it your dad?

22:15.147 --> 22:16.815
- Let me say hi.
- Okay, Dad.

22:17.441 --> 22:19.944
I said I wanted to say hi.

22:20.986 --> 22:22.696
Oh, I didn't hear you.

22:23.739 --> 22:25.532
- Sorry.
- Gosh.

22:26.909 --> 22:28.993
Ta-da. It's pumpkin porridge.

22:28.994 --> 22:32.873
It's rich in beta-carotene and vitamin A,
so it'll help with the inflammation.

22:33.457 --> 22:34.792
Make sure to eat everything.

22:43.717 --> 22:45.594
- Hadam.
- Yes?

22:46.178 --> 22:48.429
You know I like you so, so much, right?

22:48.430 --> 22:50.557
You helped me stay strong
when I was in pain.

22:51.308 --> 22:53.726
If you ever have a hard time someday,

22:53.727 --> 22:57.313
I'll do the same for you
so that you stay strong.

22:57.314 --> 22:59.440
Sure.

22:59.441 --> 23:02.151
But that's not going to happen.

23:02.152 --> 23:04.779
Once you're better,
I'll have nothing but happy days ahead.

23:27.678 --> 23:28.845
Hi.

23:28.846 --> 23:31.389
- Did you have a good weekend?
- Yes.

23:31.390 --> 23:33.391
I'm on my way to meet Mr. Chae.

23:33.392 --> 23:36.394
He sent me files on the material,
but they kept getting corrupted,

23:36.395 --> 23:37.854
so he's bringing them in person.

23:37.855 --> 23:39.606
He must have something to cover nearby.

23:40.691 --> 23:42.608
That's quite a coincidence.

23:45.529 --> 23:49.157
Ah. I was checking the sample dye
from the color team.

23:49.158 --> 23:50.617
I guess it wasn't dry yet.

23:51.660 --> 23:53.328
I'll get going, then.

23:55.622 --> 23:58.667
I felt so awkward
I ended up rambling.

24:10.137 --> 24:12.930
Um… These are the colors
that Ms. Kim directed.

24:12.931 --> 24:15.683
Then this would be the most similar,

24:15.684 --> 24:18.436
but it might look muted on the fabric.

24:18.437 --> 24:19.562
I think so, too.

24:19.563 --> 24:21.564
We should try mixing the colors again.

24:21.565 --> 24:24.525
Then let's apply the feedback
and submit a report for now.

24:24.526 --> 24:26.611
Okay.

24:26.612 --> 24:27.820
Coffee?

24:27.821 --> 24:29.530
All right, everyone.

24:29.531 --> 24:31.491
Fresh coffee.

24:31.492 --> 24:33.367
- Mr. Park.
- Hello.

24:33.368 --> 24:34.619
What brings you here?

24:34.620 --> 24:36.579
I got a new batch of beans.

24:36.580 --> 24:37.830
Gosh.

24:37.831 --> 24:41.960
So I thought I'd deliver some
to my regular customers.

24:42.628 --> 24:44.378
Thank you.

24:44.379 --> 24:46.714
-  No problem.
- I'm taking this one.

24:46.715 --> 24:48.424
It's totally my style.

24:48.425 --> 24:50.051
Oh, I'm sorry.

24:50.052 --> 24:53.346
This is reserved for someone else.

24:53.347 --> 24:55.223
- Take this.
- Okay.

24:56.517 --> 24:58.810
Too bad. Ribbons are my signature.

25:01.188 --> 25:04.565
You brought coffee for everyone
since it'll be too obvious, right?

25:04.566 --> 25:05.900
Oh…

25:05.901 --> 25:07.735
- Could you tell?
- Yes.

25:10.114 --> 25:11.781
How was your trip to Chuncheon?

25:11.782 --> 25:14.075
Grandma was so excited to go.

25:14.076 --> 25:16.828
Uh… Of course.

25:16.829 --> 25:17.913
We had a great time.

25:19.331 --> 25:21.833
By the way, is Mr. Seonu okay?

25:21.834 --> 25:23.918
I didn't call
since I didn't want to bother him.

25:23.919 --> 25:26.547
What? Did something happen?

25:27.131 --> 25:30.384
He clearly doesn't seem well,
but he won't tell me.

25:33.220 --> 25:35.930
Some people have a hard time

25:35.931 --> 25:38.350
sharing things when they care
about someone deeply.

25:40.477 --> 25:41.979
I can guarantee you

25:42.521 --> 25:46.524
that when Chan
really has to tell you something,

25:46.525 --> 25:48.152
he'll tell you honestly

25:49.027 --> 25:50.653
without hiding it.

25:51.864 --> 25:55.450
So just trust him
and wait patiently for that moment.

25:57.703 --> 25:58.704
All right.

26:00.497 --> 26:01.498
Mmm.

26:05.127 --> 26:06.879
I startled you in Chuncheon, didn't I?

26:07.462 --> 26:10.173
I was startled too and acted like a child.

26:10.174 --> 26:11.257
I'm sorry.

26:11.258 --> 26:13.844
But you don't have to worry.

26:14.803 --> 26:16.512
I already planned everything.

26:16.513 --> 26:18.932
What plan? To disappear on your own?

26:20.767 --> 26:22.269
Your checkup's tomorrow, right?

26:23.478 --> 26:25.647
You have to take me with you.

26:26.523 --> 26:29.025
How did you know the date?

26:29.026 --> 26:30.651
I met Yougyum.

26:30.652 --> 26:34.655
He told me about the necklace
and how he's the only one who knows.

26:36.825 --> 26:38.075
I see.

26:38.076 --> 26:41.787
But I'm not a child, you know.

26:41.788 --> 26:44.041
- I can go by myself--
- Nabong.

26:45.167 --> 26:48.086
You don't have to act tough
in front of me.

26:50.172 --> 26:51.215
I told you,

26:52.549 --> 26:54.551
I won't let you be alone.

26:58.889 --> 27:00.057
I guess this is why

27:01.558 --> 27:03.060
we met after 50 years.

27:04.811 --> 27:07.731
You have no one to rely on,
and have so many things to protect.

27:10.484 --> 27:11.693
I'll protect you,

27:13.403 --> 27:14.488
so you can rely on me.

27:15.489 --> 27:17.157
I'll stay by your side.

27:31.588 --> 27:32.673
Hmm?

27:35.217 --> 27:37.344
What is all this?

27:40.180 --> 27:42.890
You have to handle
everything on the desk in my place.

27:42.891 --> 27:44.016
Finish them by today.

27:46.645 --> 27:48.187
Hello? Ms. Kim--

27:48.188 --> 27:51.148
Among the 12 SS candidate outfits,
the six I picked are fixed.

27:51.149 --> 27:53.275
Pick the other six.

27:53.276 --> 27:56.821
Submit a report on which to pick
and the reasons by today.

27:56.822 --> 27:58.322
What? But--

27:58.323 --> 28:00.533
You saw the pigment samples
yesterday, right?

28:00.534 --> 28:03.536
Organize the differences in color
and decide which one to go with.

28:03.537 --> 28:06.163
And the differences by fabric.
Send it by today.

28:06.164 --> 28:07.915
Wait, Ms. Kim. I--

28:07.916 --> 28:10.876
I received two drafts
of the press kit for Paris.

28:10.877 --> 28:13.754
Choose the one that suits our image
and give it to Mr. Yeon.

28:13.755 --> 28:16.716
I have work outside the office,
so I won't be there today.

28:16.717 --> 28:19.218
Finish everything by today
and send it to me by email.

28:19.219 --> 28:22.346
- All of that by today?
- Are you saying you can't?

28:22.347 --> 28:24.181
Did you forget?
I told you to take my workload.

28:24.182 --> 28:25.684
But still, this is…

28:31.314 --> 28:32.399
Mr. Park!

28:40.157 --> 28:43.076
Hmm?
He didn't mention anything.

28:44.703 --> 28:45.704
Genius.

28:47.831 --> 28:50.250
Do you know where Mr. Park went?

28:51.376 --> 28:52.377
Hmm?

28:53.503 --> 28:55.338
Where did he go?

28:57.591 --> 29:01.178
Ms. Kim, can you confirm the materials…

29:01.803 --> 29:02.887
Ah…

29:02.888 --> 29:04.638
Right, she's at a meeting.

29:04.639 --> 29:05.682
Okay.

29:09.019 --> 29:11.813
I can't believe this.
Hayeong, you klutz.

29:14.608 --> 29:15.650
Goodness.

29:16.401 --> 29:17.402
What is this?

29:20.655 --> 29:23.240
DON'T CAUSE TROUBLE FOR MY GRANDDAUGHTERS
I'M STILL OKAY

29:23.241 --> 29:25.159
KEEP GLASSES IN FRONT OF THE MONITOR

29:25.160 --> 29:27.203
DON'T TAKE OFF YOUGYUM'S NECKLACE!

29:29.956 --> 29:32.584
"Noble Life Center"?

29:40.550 --> 29:42.511
NOBLE LIFE CENTER
COUNSELING CENTER

29:47.099 --> 29:48.432
Secure retirement.

29:48.433 --> 29:51.603
This is the Noble Life Center,
Korea's premium senior care center.

29:52.312 --> 29:54.689
Hello, this is Noble Life Center.

29:55.816 --> 29:57.734
I…

29:59.486 --> 30:00.487
I mean,

30:02.030 --> 30:03.031
I wanted

30:03.865 --> 30:07.535
to check my reservation.

30:07.536 --> 30:08.703
What is your name?

30:10.956 --> 30:14.375
I'm Kim Nabong's guardian.

30:14.376 --> 30:16.001
Right, Kim Nabong.

30:16.002 --> 30:18.588
She's still set to move in
at the end of June, right?

30:19.339 --> 30:21.298
You wanted a single room

30:21.299 --> 30:23.843
and signed up for the specialized
dementia care, right?

30:23.844 --> 30:26.513
CLOSET KEY, JEWELRY BOX

30:27.430 --> 30:29.099
"Closet key, jewelry box…"

30:44.823 --> 30:47.074
I really don't need lunch.

30:47.075 --> 30:49.953
When do I finish all of this?

30:55.458 --> 30:56.710
Hayeong.

30:59.880 --> 31:01.255
What is it?

31:01.256 --> 31:03.133
What's wrong? Huh?

31:04.217 --> 31:06.136
What do we do?

31:06.887 --> 31:09.097
What do we do about Grandma?

31:09.681 --> 31:12.057
What about Grandma? What's going on?

31:16.438 --> 31:17.647
What is this?

31:23.111 --> 31:25.739
NOBLE LIFE CENTER
CALL TO CONFIRM RESERVATION ON THE 17TH!

31:33.246 --> 31:35.957
What do you mean?
Why would she go to a care center?

31:37.292 --> 31:41.045
I know you're just playing a joke
since my CSAT is over.

31:41.046 --> 31:43.381
- Hadam.
- That doesn't make any sense.

31:44.174 --> 31:45.425
Why would Grandma…

31:45.967 --> 31:48.677
Why would she go there?

31:48.678 --> 31:51.890
I think she was trying
to leave quietly.

31:53.850 --> 31:55.560
She must have been planning it

31:56.311 --> 31:58.188
for quite a long time.

32:27.259 --> 32:28.843
This was in here.

32:41.398 --> 32:43.316
To my beloved granddaughters.

32:43.900 --> 32:47.653
Bonjour, my beautiful granddaughters
who took after me.

32:47.654 --> 32:49.780
By the time you've opened this,

32:49.781 --> 32:52.658
I'll probably be having champagne

32:52.659 --> 32:54.661
on a plane to southern France.

32:55.745 --> 32:57.204
Don't move, ma'am.

32:57.205 --> 32:59.457
Don't be too upset.

33:00.083 --> 33:04.211
I want to reward myself
for working hard all these years.

33:04.212 --> 33:06.130
So I'm really happy.

33:06.131 --> 33:08.632
-  Please curl your back.
-  Oh.

33:08.633 --> 33:11.802
And don't try to visit me.

33:11.803 --> 33:14.179
I had such a hard time in my 20s

33:14.180 --> 33:16.598
attending fashion school
with a baby on my back.

33:16.599 --> 33:18.476
And I didn't get to try so many things

33:19.060 --> 33:21.896
because I had no money or time.

33:22.397 --> 33:26.818
I'm going to be extremely busy
doing everything I couldn't do back then.

33:27.736 --> 33:29.111
So please…

33:29.112 --> 33:30.404
-  Ms. Kim Nabong.
- Yes.

33:30.405 --> 33:32.948
-  Let me enjoy my life here.
- Head to the next room.

33:32.949 --> 33:37.120
Ah. And as for those
wedding gowns…

33:46.880 --> 33:51.425
Your grandma's the famous Kim Nana,

33:51.426 --> 33:54.471
so letting you wear wedding gowns
made by someone else?

33:54.971 --> 33:56.347
Oh, no.

33:56.348 --> 33:57.974
I can never let that happen.

33:59.976 --> 34:03.103
I thought I'd be too busy
having fun in France

34:03.104 --> 34:05.022
to make any clothes,

34:05.023 --> 34:06.358
so I made them in advance.

34:07.108 --> 34:10.445
I just made them easily in my spare time.

34:12.906 --> 34:15.616
Let's meet again someday

34:15.617 --> 34:17.911
after shining in each of our places.

34:18.620 --> 34:23.041
I'll be rooting for your glorious lives
from far away.

34:23.833 --> 34:25.000
Haran,

34:25.001 --> 34:26.586
Hayeong,

34:27.420 --> 34:28.505
Hadam.

34:33.134 --> 34:35.345
My life was a brilliant shade of rose

34:36.012 --> 34:40.392
because you three were my granddaughters.

34:41.726 --> 34:42.727
Take care.

34:43.228 --> 34:44.229
Au revoir.

34:45.271 --> 34:46.355
Ah.

34:46.356 --> 34:50.943
I hate saying cheesy things,
but I'm the type to say things I need to.

34:52.237 --> 34:53.238
I love you,

34:53.905 --> 34:55.865
my dear granddaughters.

34:58.284 --> 34:59.494
Why…

35:01.079 --> 35:03.123
She has three granddaughters.

35:04.374 --> 35:05.624
Why would she…

35:05.625 --> 35:07.293
It's weird that she's at a meeting.

35:08.461 --> 35:09.713
Where is she right now?

35:10.880 --> 35:12.424
She hasn't left already, has she?

35:21.599 --> 35:24.893
SECRET WITH YOUGYUM
DON'T TAKE OFF YOUGYUM'S NECKLACE!

35:26.187 --> 35:28.522
Why don't you spend some time
with your grandma--

35:28.523 --> 35:30.983
Why are you suddenly
bringing up my grandma?

35:30.984 --> 35:31.985
What?

35:32.944 --> 35:34.027
Oh…

35:34.028 --> 35:37.072
Why was your tumbler
in my grandma's study?

35:37.073 --> 35:38.866
I ran into her a while ago in the park.

35:38.867 --> 35:40.994
You know she wouldn't do such a thing.

35:48.251 --> 35:51.963
Cha Yougyum.
You knew about Grandma, didn't you?

35:52.589 --> 35:53.922
Where is she right now?

35:53.923 --> 35:57.260
I already know everything!
Just tell me!

35:58.511 --> 36:00.764
She's getting a checkup today.

36:08.062 --> 36:09.146
Over there.

36:09.147 --> 36:11.065
NEUROLOGY CENTER

36:15.236 --> 36:17.112
-  Oh.
- Hey, Manjae.

36:17.113 --> 36:18.823
- That took a while, didn't it?
-  Goodness.

36:18.948 --> 36:20.240
You did great.

36:20.241 --> 36:21.617
- Are you okay?
-  Yes.

36:29.459 --> 36:30.918
How can you…

36:30.919 --> 36:33.086
Of all people, how can you do this to me?

36:33.087 --> 36:34.713
Why are you--

36:34.714 --> 36:36.632
You should take some of my workload.

36:36.633 --> 36:38.425
Let me get some rest, too.

36:38.426 --> 36:40.969
He's not keeping it from you.
He probably can't.

36:40.970 --> 36:43.764
He probably doesn't want
to burden you with his pain.

36:43.765 --> 36:46.392
He cares more about protecting you
than his own pain.

36:52.816 --> 36:54.107
A meeting?

36:54.108 --> 36:55.609
And what's this…

36:55.610 --> 36:56.611
I'll do it.

37:02.617 --> 37:03.784
What was that, Grandma?

37:03.785 --> 37:06.119
You didn't even look at him
and didn't say a word.

37:06.120 --> 37:08.372
He left because
you made him uncomfortable.

37:08.373 --> 37:11.376
Did Grandma summon you
and threaten you or something?

37:23.638 --> 37:25.598
DON'T CAUSE TROUBLE FOR MY GRANDDAUGHTERS

37:38.570 --> 37:39.571
Grandma.

37:48.079 --> 37:49.205
I'm okay.

37:49.789 --> 37:50.790
It's all right.

37:54.043 --> 37:56.503
Ms. Kim Nabong.
Please go to the next room.

37:56.504 --> 37:57.547
Okay.

37:58.840 --> 38:00.215
I'll be back.

38:00.216 --> 38:01.301
Let's go.

38:11.019 --> 38:13.437
You've a lot of granddaughters.

38:13.438 --> 38:14.938
All right.

38:14.939 --> 38:15.940
See you in a bit.

38:31.956 --> 38:35.918
Make sure to keep it dry,
and tell me if it's too tight.

38:35.919 --> 38:37.170
Okay. Thank you.

38:39.088 --> 38:40.172
Are you okay?

38:40.173 --> 38:41.674
I'm fine.

38:42.842 --> 38:45.093
You need some vitamins.
I'll peel these for you.

38:45.094 --> 38:47.471
- It's fine, I'll do it.
- Mmm-mmm.

38:47.472 --> 38:49.724
- Ah…
-  Cha Yougyum!

38:52.435 --> 38:53.436
Bye.

38:57.231 --> 38:58.232
Hadam…

39:00.985 --> 39:03.445
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
about your grandma.

39:03.446 --> 39:05.114
She said…

39:08.826 --> 39:10.953
Thank you, Yougyum.

39:12.038 --> 39:13.456
Thank you so much.

39:14.582 --> 39:17.751
Yougyum has been taking care of her.

39:17.752 --> 39:19.544
Without the necklace he gave her,

39:19.545 --> 39:22.382
I would've lost her in Chuncheon.

39:23.508 --> 39:27.053
It must have been tough
keeping that secret on his own.

39:27.762 --> 39:30.348
She would've had a hard time on her own.

39:32.141 --> 39:33.142
Thank you

39:33.893 --> 39:35.561
for taking care of her.

39:41.943 --> 39:43.277
Sorry, I didn't tell you.

39:43.820 --> 39:45.238
You must've been shocked.

39:46.656 --> 39:47.657
Thank you.

39:48.992 --> 39:51.411
Thank you so, so much, Yougyum.

39:55.456 --> 39:58.084
Let's go see her.

40:19.397 --> 40:20.398
I didn't know.

40:22.650 --> 40:24.610
I should've known,

40:26.279 --> 40:27.280
but I didn't.

40:27.947 --> 40:28.948
Why?

40:29.490 --> 40:31.534
How could you not know?

40:32.285 --> 40:34.828
It was you of all people.

40:34.829 --> 40:36.330
You said she was your savior,

40:37.165 --> 40:38.874
and you promised to take care of her.

40:38.875 --> 40:41.293
You were always by her side.
How could you not know?

40:43.171 --> 40:45.840
When I asked if anything happened
in Seongsu-dong,

40:46.674 --> 40:47.967
why did you hide it from me?

40:48.843 --> 40:51.178
No, if you weren't going to tell me,

40:51.179 --> 40:53.388
shouldn't you have
looked into it more, at least?

40:53.389 --> 40:55.266
If you'd found out then…

40:56.184 --> 40:57.185
I'm sorry.

40:58.352 --> 40:59.353
No.

41:00.188 --> 41:01.606
Pretend you didn't hear that.

41:02.565 --> 41:03.983
What I just said

41:04.776 --> 41:06.944
is actually what I want to say to myself.

41:09.197 --> 41:11.407
I know it's not your fault,

41:11.991 --> 41:16.079
but I feel so pathetic and stupid.

41:17.580 --> 41:19.832
So I don't know what to do.

41:21.084 --> 41:23.294
I should've known.

41:24.504 --> 41:25.505
I'm sorry…

41:26.380 --> 41:27.632
I yelled at you.

41:38.851 --> 41:39.976
Sorry.

41:46.692 --> 41:47.860
He's not picking up.

41:48.861 --> 41:50.737
Mr. Park, where are you?

41:50.738 --> 41:53.491
Customers are coming in,
asking why you're closed today.

41:55.868 --> 41:56.869
The hospital?

41:58.955 --> 42:00.372
Then what about…

42:00.373 --> 42:02.542
What about Ms. Song?

42:03.167 --> 42:06.336
The MRI shows
normal intracranial pressure,

42:06.337 --> 42:09.422
but the ventricles
are significantly enlarged.

42:09.423 --> 42:12.092
We also ran a cerebrospinal fluid test
to double-check,

42:12.093 --> 42:13.636
and the results show…

42:16.264 --> 42:17.515
that it's not dementia.

42:18.724 --> 42:20.350
Really?

42:20.351 --> 42:21.685
That's such a relief.

42:21.686 --> 42:25.647
But we suspect
normal pressure hydrocephalus.

42:25.648 --> 42:27.315
Hydrocephalus?

42:27.316 --> 42:30.193
It occurs when cerebrospinal fluid
isn't properly absorbed,

42:30.194 --> 42:34.030
leading to symptoms like memory loss
and problems with walking.

42:34.031 --> 42:36.992
The symptoms are similar,
so some mistake it for dementia.

42:36.993 --> 42:38.326
I see.

42:38.327 --> 42:41.164
Have you had any problems
with walking recently?

42:42.290 --> 42:45.042
- I don't think I've seen…
- I'm not sure…

42:45.543 --> 42:46.751
-  Oh!
-  Oh gosh.

42:46.752 --> 42:50.463
She did. Last time,
you had bruises on your legs.

42:50.464 --> 42:52.674
Huh? Did you hit your leg somewhere?

42:52.675 --> 42:55.428
It's fine. I just fell.
My legs suddenly wouldn't listen.

42:56.179 --> 42:58.680
Patients usually show a response
within 24 hours,

42:58.681 --> 43:01.391
even within 10 hours
after draining the cerebrospinal fluid.

43:01.392 --> 43:03.935
We'll be able to confirm this
after the gait test.

43:03.936 --> 43:06.189
So let's see
how much improvement there is.

43:06.981 --> 43:09.733
You can see how you sometimes
had narrower strides

43:09.734 --> 43:12.360
and dragged your feet
in the morning, right?

43:12.361 --> 43:14.906
But it improved significantly
after draining the fluid.

43:15.948 --> 43:18.992
The tap test confirms
normal pressure hydrocephalus.

43:18.993 --> 43:22.621
She can get better
with treatment, right?

43:22.622 --> 43:24.497
With successful surgery,
she should improve.

43:24.498 --> 43:25.999
All right.

43:26.000 --> 43:28.418
We'll create a small opening in the skull

43:28.419 --> 43:31.338
and insert a thin tube called a shunt
into the ventricle

43:31.339 --> 43:34.925
to drain excess cerebrospinal fluid
into the abdomen.

43:34.926 --> 43:36.509
Ah…

43:36.510 --> 43:39.763
Given your age, I suggest
getting hospitalized a few days in advance

43:39.764 --> 43:41.432
to run some basic tests first.

43:42.099 --> 43:43.600
Proceed with the admission,

43:43.601 --> 43:46.937
and we'll set the surgery date
based on your condition.

43:48.481 --> 43:50.982
The admission's done already?

43:50.983 --> 43:55.528
Yes, a tall man in a suit
came and finished the process.

43:55.529 --> 43:57.031
He even paid the fees.

44:00.868 --> 44:02.035
Mr. Yeon.

44:28.229 --> 44:29.354
Cha Yougyum.

44:29.355 --> 44:30.438
Yes, Ms. Kim.

44:30.439 --> 44:34.359
You're an athlete.
Go take care of your own condition.

44:34.360 --> 44:35.610
You need to recover.

44:35.611 --> 44:37.446
- Song Hadam.
- Yes?

44:38.072 --> 44:39.365
You said you'd help him.

44:39.865 --> 44:41.659
Stay right by his side.

44:42.660 --> 44:43.703
And…

44:44.829 --> 44:46.413
Song Haran, Song Hayeong.

44:46.414 --> 44:50.458
No, Lead Designer Song,
Designer Song Hayeong.

44:50.459 --> 44:55.213
If anything at my company
goes wrong while I'm away,

44:55.214 --> 44:56.631
I'm kicking all of you out.

44:56.632 --> 44:58.425
So focus on work from now on.

44:58.426 --> 45:00.677
Don't even think about coming here.

45:00.678 --> 45:01.971
But…

45:02.555 --> 45:03.638
Okay.

45:03.639 --> 45:06.391
I'll be taking care of her
from now on,

45:06.392 --> 45:09.853
so you youngsters
go and focus on your own stuff.

45:09.854 --> 45:12.230
We'll take turns coming here.
You have your coffee shop.

45:12.231 --> 45:13.315
Mmm-mmm.

45:13.316 --> 45:15.692
SHIM is temporarily closed
until she gets surgery

45:15.693 --> 45:18.528
and recovers well.

45:18.529 --> 45:20.071
I'll think of this as winter vacation

45:20.072 --> 45:23.450
and enjoy my time here with my old friend.

45:24.660 --> 45:27.121
All right. Everyone, stop bothering us.

45:28.205 --> 45:30.832
But where did Mr. Yeon go?

45:30.833 --> 45:33.293
- I thought I saw him in the hallway.
-  Oh.

45:33.294 --> 45:35.378
He'll probably be busy
taking care of things

45:35.379 --> 45:36.922
in Grandma's place.

45:47.058 --> 45:48.100
Oh?

45:51.479 --> 45:53.981
I'm sorry, I took so long.

45:54.648 --> 45:56.066
How did you know?

45:56.067 --> 45:58.777
I heard from Mr. Park just a while ago.

45:58.778 --> 46:01.488
I'm sure her surgery will go well.

46:02.740 --> 46:08.287
I wish the people I love won't feel pain,
physically or mentally.

46:08.871 --> 46:10.663
I'm sure she'll overcome this.

46:10.664 --> 46:12.624
So don't get too scared.

46:12.625 --> 46:13.959
Everything will be all right.

46:14.502 --> 46:18.463
Sorry, but can we stay like this
for 10 more seconds?

46:18.464 --> 46:21.926
We can stay like this for 10 minutes
or even 10 hours.

46:22.718 --> 46:25.345
Sorry,
I didn't contact you sooner.

46:25.346 --> 46:26.597
Things were so hectic.

46:27.348 --> 46:28.349
Oh?

46:29.600 --> 46:31.810
I'll be upset if you feel sorry over this.

46:33.521 --> 46:34.814
You must've missed lunch.

46:35.606 --> 46:37.232
Wait here, I'll get you something.

46:37.233 --> 46:41.319
Then can I just get some coffee?
I don't think I can eat anything.

46:41.320 --> 46:43.114
All right. Hang on.

46:43.697 --> 46:46.742
Why are you dressed so lightly?

46:48.536 --> 46:51.913
This cardigan is really valuable to me,

46:51.914 --> 46:54.290
so I don't usually lend it to anyone.

46:54.291 --> 46:56.293
But I'll let you wear it just this once.

47:00.589 --> 47:01.590
Don't ruin it.

47:12.351 --> 47:13.352
We meet again.

47:14.562 --> 47:16.147
Oh. Hello.

47:16.730 --> 47:20.108
My grandma's getting hospitalized here
for a few days.

47:20.109 --> 47:21.569
Ah. Really?

47:22.111 --> 47:25.822
Oh, um… I accidentally took
one of your bracelet charms.

47:25.823 --> 47:28.074
I'll give it back to you
when I visit tomorrow.

47:28.075 --> 47:30.577
Really? I was wondering
where that charm went.

47:30.578 --> 47:32.913
That's great. But…

47:33.456 --> 47:35.249
the man who was with you last time…

47:37.084 --> 47:38.461
Is he your boyfriend?

47:39.295 --> 47:40.879
Yes. Why do you ask?

47:40.880 --> 47:42.256
You looked good together.

47:43.007 --> 47:46.176
He reminded me of someone I used to know.

47:46.177 --> 47:47.887
Ah.

47:48.471 --> 47:50.931
Oh… You're a neurology doctor.

47:51.807 --> 47:54.476
My grandmother's getting surgery
for hydrocephalus.

47:54.477 --> 47:56.144
Please take good care of her.

47:56.145 --> 47:59.064
I'm only visiting, so I'm not authorized
to treat patients directly.

48:01.650 --> 48:02.860
I came from Boston.

48:03.652 --> 48:04.653
Oh.

48:05.196 --> 48:06.571
I see.

48:06.572 --> 48:08.406
The neurosurgeons
will take good care of her.

48:08.407 --> 48:11.535
The neurology department
will see the results, so I'll check.

48:12.119 --> 48:13.454
And my bracelet…

48:14.163 --> 48:15.581
I was worried

48:16.457 --> 48:19.251
about the gap in my bracelet.

48:19.877 --> 48:22.295
I'm glad you'll give it back to me.

48:22.296 --> 48:24.298
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

48:25.424 --> 48:26.425
Bye.

48:29.970 --> 48:31.013
You're back.

48:36.810 --> 48:38.353
Yes, Mr. Park.

48:38.354 --> 48:40.897
Oh, I met Mr. Seonu in the lobby.

48:40.898 --> 48:42.233
Really?

48:42.900 --> 48:43.983
Okay.

48:43.984 --> 48:47.654
Grandma said
she wants to talk to you alone.

48:47.655 --> 48:49.072
Is that okay?

48:49.073 --> 48:51.992
- If you feel uncomfortable…
-  No, it's fine.

48:55.996 --> 48:58.915
I should have put more thought
into what you said that day.

48:58.916 --> 49:00.625
I'm sorry, Ms. Kim.

49:00.626 --> 49:02.043
"That day"?

49:02.044 --> 49:04.295
Thanks to you,
I'll be able to leave in peace.

49:04.296 --> 49:05.673
Are you going somewhere?

49:06.799 --> 49:09.802
I'm planning to stay in France
after I retire.

49:13.013 --> 49:15.140
I hid this on purpose.

49:15.766 --> 49:17.434
How could you have known?

49:19.603 --> 49:20.604
Are you all right?

49:21.188 --> 49:22.565
I'm fine.

49:24.191 --> 49:25.192
But…

49:25.734 --> 49:27.610
I'd like to ask you the same thing.

49:27.611 --> 49:29.029
I heard about your head.

49:30.239 --> 49:31.574
Are you sure you're okay?

49:33.117 --> 49:34.118
I'm fine.

49:35.035 --> 49:36.160
No,

49:36.161 --> 49:38.330
I'm going to make sure I'm fine

49:38.998 --> 49:41.250
so I can stay by Ms. Song's side.

49:42.126 --> 49:44.253
My head, and everything else…

49:46.797 --> 49:48.214
I'm going to make it all okay.

49:50.968 --> 49:51.969
Haran cares…

49:53.470 --> 49:55.305
for you a lot.

49:55.306 --> 49:58.392
It actually surprised me
how sincere she is about you.

49:59.018 --> 50:02.104
And she seems to be
thinking of a future with you.

50:03.355 --> 50:06.482
I know, and I feel the same way.

50:06.483 --> 50:07.860
I want to see you two

50:09.278 --> 50:11.739
getting along well for as long as I can.

50:12.990 --> 50:16.452
At least for Haran's sake and your sake,

50:17.953 --> 50:19.330
make sure you're okay.

50:23.167 --> 50:24.168
I will.

50:27.796 --> 50:29.505
Thanks for coming.

50:29.506 --> 50:32.175
Oh. When's your checkup again?

50:32.176 --> 50:33.259
Next week.

50:33.260 --> 50:35.470
It'll be fine, so don't worry about me.

50:35.471 --> 50:36.805
Take good care of Ms. Kim.

50:37.389 --> 50:38.473
I'll get going now.

50:38.474 --> 50:40.142
- Right, your cardigan.
- Ah…

50:41.143 --> 50:42.811
Keep it on. You'll catch a cold.

50:45.314 --> 50:46.523
Don't worry.

50:50.527 --> 50:51.987
Grandma was right.

50:53.113 --> 50:56.824
Having just one person to lean on

50:56.825 --> 50:58.202
will help you stay strong.

51:02.331 --> 51:05.041
I do have a pretty broad back.

51:05.042 --> 51:06.376
When did you notice?

51:06.377 --> 51:08.711
Should I leave my back here
for you to lean on?

51:11.048 --> 51:13.716
- Go.
- Okay. I'll go now.

51:13.717 --> 51:14.718
Bye.

51:18.263 --> 51:19.348
Head back inside.

51:39.618 --> 51:40.619
Let me talk to you.

51:41.912 --> 51:43.413
What do you think you're doing?

51:43.414 --> 51:45.123
Stop messing with her.

51:45.124 --> 51:46.792
The thing you wanted to protect…

51:48.335 --> 51:49.336
was her?

51:50.045 --> 51:52.423
Are you worried you'll lose her
if I say something?

51:53.424 --> 51:54.757
Does she know

51:54.758 --> 51:58.261
that you went to the same school
as Hyeokchan and were his roommate?

51:58.262 --> 51:59.263
Does she know who you are?

52:00.597 --> 52:03.391
Hyeokchan's dead, but you're alive,

52:03.392 --> 52:05.978
and the person you want to protect
is his old girlfriend?

52:07.146 --> 52:08.271
That's funny.

52:08.272 --> 52:09.355
Since when?

52:09.356 --> 52:11.107
Did you have feelings for her then?

52:11.108 --> 52:13.151
You must've jumped at the chance
when he died.

52:13.152 --> 52:14.944
Don't say it like that.

52:14.945 --> 52:16.321
That's not the case.

52:17.364 --> 52:20.367
She's going through a hard time right now.

52:20.993 --> 52:23.287
Don't say things that…

52:24.329 --> 52:25.788
will only dig up old wounds.

52:25.789 --> 52:27.290
Please.

52:27.291 --> 52:29.460
Why should I do that for you?

52:32.629 --> 52:33.797
I remembered something.

52:34.673 --> 52:36.258
The day that the waste container fell,

52:37.634 --> 52:39.469
you were in the lab as well.

52:39.470 --> 52:41.137
And you were shouting at him to stop.

52:44.183 --> 52:47.393
I don't have the time
to answer all your questions.

52:47.394 --> 52:49.980
Why was the waste container
next to Hyeokchan?

52:52.232 --> 52:54.358
The day Hyeokchan's lip was busted…

52:54.359 --> 52:55.444
Was that day

52:56.153 --> 52:58.113
the day of the accident?

52:59.323 --> 53:02.200
I didn't have any memories
of that day until now,

53:02.201 --> 53:04.202
but it feels like it's from that day.

53:04.203 --> 53:08.123
Tell me what happened in the lab that day.

53:09.500 --> 53:10.501
You know what happened.

53:12.211 --> 53:14.879
You can't tell Haran the truth.

53:14.880 --> 53:16.214
No, you're not telling her.

53:16.215 --> 53:18.925
So why are you so obsessed
with finding out what happened?

53:18.926 --> 53:21.385
If everyone involved
has the right to know,

53:21.386 --> 53:24.973
shouldn't Haran also know
that you're fake?

53:25.933 --> 53:27.475
I'm going to tell her.

53:27.476 --> 53:30.061
- But right now--
- If you go and tell her first,

53:30.062 --> 53:32.773
then I might think about telling you, too.

53:40.864 --> 53:42.031
Please.

53:42.032 --> 53:44.076
Stop asking me strange questions.

53:44.868 --> 53:46.244
If you provoke me,

53:46.245 --> 53:49.790
even I don't know
what I'll end up telling her.

53:57.756 --> 53:58.882
Hey, Kang Hyeokchan.

53:59.675 --> 54:01.300
I have to tell you something.

54:01.301 --> 54:04.804
I've been chatting with your girlfriend.

54:04.805 --> 54:06.557
She thinks she's been talking to you.

54:07.140 --> 54:08.391
You were pretending to be me?

54:08.392 --> 54:09.976
Do you have any idea what you've done?

54:11.311 --> 54:13.312
- I'm sorry.
-  Did you have feelings for her?

54:13.313 --> 54:15.022
You must've jumped at the chance.

54:15.023 --> 54:17.401
Shouldn't Haran also know
that you're fake?

54:22.906 --> 54:24.199
I told him…

54:24.783 --> 54:26.034
I told Hyeokchan everything.

54:26.869 --> 54:27.870
But…

54:29.204 --> 54:31.164
what happened after that?

54:46.221 --> 54:47.973
I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

54:48.849 --> 54:50.142
It's all my fault.

54:51.143 --> 54:52.185
"Fault…"

54:59.276 --> 55:01.153
-  Nineteen.
- Nineteen.

55:01.737 --> 55:04.530
-  Thirty-one point five.
- Thirty-one point five.

55:04.531 --> 55:06.741
Everyone, let's keep our spirits up.

55:06.742 --> 55:08.618
When Ms. Kim comes back,

55:08.619 --> 55:11.662
we should show her how much we did
to put her mind at ease.

55:11.663 --> 55:13.789
So how about a quick cheer?

55:13.790 --> 55:15.542
No, forget it.

55:16.793 --> 55:18.878
One, two, three.

55:18.879 --> 55:20.130
Let's do this!

55:21.173 --> 55:22.423
Let's do this!

55:22.424 --> 55:23.674
Whatever it is.

55:23.675 --> 55:24.759
- Hey.
- It's Chan.

55:24.760 --> 55:26.802
What's the occasion?
There's no meeting today.

55:26.803 --> 55:29.096
We got the additional script,
so I dropped by.

55:29.097 --> 55:32.516
And since SHIM is closed,
I made these myself.

55:32.517 --> 55:33.643
I can't guarantee the taste.

55:33.644 --> 55:35.061
- Thank you.
-  Thank you.

55:35.062 --> 55:38.814
But Ms. Song isn't here right now.

55:38.815 --> 55:40.024
Really?

55:40.025 --> 55:42.610
- Where did she go?
- She took the afternoon off.

55:42.611 --> 55:46.405
Even if Ms. Kim told her not to come,
I guess she's pretty worried.

55:46.406 --> 55:47.823
Did she go to the hospital?

55:47.824 --> 55:50.284
No, she said she had to drop by somewhere.

55:50.285 --> 55:52.953
She had to return something to someone.

55:52.954 --> 55:53.955
Oh…

55:54.706 --> 55:56.165
And my bracelet…

55:56.166 --> 55:58.125
I'm glad you'll give it back to me.

55:58.126 --> 55:59.794
I'll see you tomorrow.

56:02.172 --> 56:06.635
Sunyul National
University Hospital is 1.5 km ahead.

56:10.806 --> 56:13.392
Does she know who you are?

56:16.311 --> 56:17.479
If you provoke me,

56:18.689 --> 56:22.401
even I don't know
what I'll end up telling her.

56:39.960 --> 56:43.462
Ah. The last patient's tone
seemed worse than the tremor.

56:43.463 --> 56:45.549
- Let's reduce the dose.
-  Okay, I'll check.

57:02.649 --> 57:04.900
- Oh. Haran.
-  You're here.

57:04.901 --> 57:08.154
Mr. Seonu's upstairs, right?
I have to give him something.

57:08.155 --> 57:09.823
He just left when I came here.

57:10.407 --> 57:11.866
He said he had to go somewhere.

57:11.867 --> 57:12.868
Oh…

57:13.702 --> 57:16.412
Then can I just leave this in his room?

57:16.413 --> 57:17.997
Sure, that's fine.

57:17.998 --> 57:21.333
I'm heading back to the hospital.
I just came to get my stuff.

57:21.334 --> 57:24.378
Then I'll give you a ride.
I'm heading there, too.

57:24.379 --> 57:26.213
No, it's fine. I called a cab.

57:26.214 --> 57:29.508
I made a lot of coffee
to share with the doctors.

57:29.509 --> 57:32.052
I'll leave one for you.

57:32.053 --> 57:35.139
Take your time drinking this
and meet Chan first.

57:35.140 --> 57:36.641
- Okay.
-  He'll be back soon.

57:38.393 --> 57:39.394
Mr. Park.

57:40.103 --> 57:41.187
Yes?

57:41.188 --> 57:43.690
Thank you for taking care of my grandma.

57:44.941 --> 57:46.777
Gosh.

57:47.527 --> 57:49.236
There's no need to thank me.

57:55.911 --> 57:58.663
TEMPORARILY CLOSED
SORRY FOR THE INCONVENIENCE

58:05.086 --> 58:07.172
Pardon me.

58:14.846 --> 58:16.765
SEONU CHAN

58:26.900 --> 58:28.026
Hey, roomie.

58:29.110 --> 58:30.319
Yes, she's here.

58:30.320 --> 58:32.489
She brought something for you,
so she went upstairs.

58:33.198 --> 58:34.907
Hang on.

58:34.908 --> 58:36.242
No, it's okay.

58:36.243 --> 58:37.952
I'll be there in a few minutes.

58:37.953 --> 58:39.245
Really?

58:39.246 --> 58:41.373
Huh? My cab's here.

58:41.873 --> 58:43.500
I'm going to the hospital,

58:44.000 --> 58:46.211
so take care of Genius for me.

58:49.005 --> 58:50.882
Is there a Post-it? Oh?

59:32.883 --> 59:33.884
Is she upstairs?

59:34.843 --> 59:36.011
Are you here?

59:37.637 --> 59:38.722
Huh?

59:42.684 --> 59:43.852
Hmm?

59:46.855 --> 59:48.189
THANKS FOR THE

01:00:22.641 --> 01:00:24.976
KANG HYEOKCHAN, GLASS TUBE, BLOOD
THAT SOUND AGAIN

01:00:34.778 --> 01:00:37.614
KANG HYEOKCHAN HOSPITALIZED, WOMAN
THAT SOUND WAS HER BRACELET

01:00:39.449 --> 01:00:41.700
I'll tell her everything

01:00:41.701 --> 01:00:43.161
and apologize to her.

01:00:44.162 --> 01:00:45.621
I want to tell her everything

01:00:45.622 --> 01:00:48.500
and love her as my true self…

01:00:50.085 --> 01:00:51.086
from now on.

01:00:51.962 --> 01:00:53.004
Before it's too late.

01:01:12.273 --> 01:01:13.691
Chan.

01:01:13.692 --> 01:01:15.150
Why did you come back?

01:01:15.151 --> 01:01:16.527
Well…

01:01:16.528 --> 01:01:19.154
Did Ms. Song come here?

01:01:19.155 --> 01:01:20.614
Hey, what's gotten into you?

01:01:20.615 --> 01:01:23.243
- We told you she's going to the hospital.
- Ah…

01:01:25.495 --> 01:01:26.496
All right.

01:01:29.290 --> 01:01:33.585
Mr. Park, is Ms. Song
at the hospital right now?

01:01:33.586 --> 01:01:35.462
No, she's not here.

01:01:35.463 --> 01:01:38.257
Did you not see her?

01:01:38.258 --> 01:01:39.300
Oh…

01:01:40.301 --> 01:01:41.678
It's nothing. Never mind.

01:01:59.988 --> 01:02:02.115
RAN

01:02:08.329 --> 01:02:09.872
Are you home?

01:02:09.873 --> 01:02:11.415
If you're home, come out.

01:02:11.416 --> 01:02:13.542
Let's meet. Let's meet up and talk.

01:02:13.543 --> 01:02:14.961
I'll explain everything.

01:02:53.833 --> 01:02:55.418
- Hey…
-  Don't come any closer.

01:03:04.636 --> 01:03:06.179
Boston Institute of Technology.

01:03:07.722 --> 01:03:09.432
Kang Hyeokchan's roommate.

01:03:10.892 --> 01:03:12.268
Have you really known me

01:03:13.394 --> 01:03:15.105
for seven years?

01:03:21.277 --> 01:03:22.946
- Song Haran.
- Don't say my name.

01:03:26.157 --> 01:03:27.408
Did you have fun

01:03:28.701 --> 01:03:30.328
pretending to be Kang Hyeokchan?

01:03:41.840 --> 01:03:43.800
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:04:07.907 --> 01:04:10.993
She found out about everything.

01:04:10.994 --> 01:04:12.744
I didn't have the chance to explain.

01:04:12.745 --> 01:04:14.622
If those two facts don't change,

01:04:15.331 --> 01:04:16.416
I won't change, either.

01:04:17.292 --> 01:04:19.001
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

01:04:19.002 --> 01:04:22.255
You don't have to look at me
or listen to me. So please,

01:04:23.006 --> 01:04:24.631
just look at this.

01:04:24.632 --> 01:04:27.134
Haran, you're burning up.

01:04:27.135 --> 01:04:29.845
You did a great job so far
working by my side.

01:04:29.846 --> 01:04:31.847
Haran's gone.

01:04:31.848 --> 01:04:34.349
You're the only one I could ask
where she could be.

01:04:34.350 --> 01:04:36.560
I have to go find her.

01:04:36.561 --> 01:04:38.563
It has to be me.

01:04:50.575 --> 01:04:51.658
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:04:51.659 --> 01:04:52.660
Translated by Juyoung Park
